headline: Analysts Get More Bullish About Walmart Stock Amid Trump Win
summary: Walmart reports earnings for its fiscal third quarter early Tuesday. Walmart stock edged lower on Monday, near record highs. Last week, several analysts raised price targets on Walmart stock, which is already sitting on a year-to-date gain of 60%.

headline: Holiday shopping promotions have been 'very strategic': Analyst
summary: As it slowly shifts into the holiday shopping season, big-name retailers Walmart (WMT), TJX (TJX), Target (TGT), Ross Stores (ROST), and Gap (GAP) are scheduled to post their latest earnings results throughout this week. Jane Hali & Associates senior research analyst Jessica Ramirez sits down with Madison Mills and Brad Smith to speak more about consumer trends heading into Black Friday and Christmas sales promotions. "[The] low-income consumer and middle-income consumer continue to be pressured as we go into the holiday season. They have been spacing out the way that they buy in order to make sure that they have their gifts for the holiday season," Ramirez explains. "And because we've had the pressure from inflation throughout the year and... from late last year, it has started to really take on savings of consumers. So it's still very tough." She elaborates that retailer promotions have also been "very strategic" in comparison to inventory levels. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.
